## Mathematical content

State that normal forms give finite certificates for semantic classification:

- a formula is satisfiable if and only if some DNF equivalent has a satisfiable term;
- a formula is a contradiction if and only if a DNF equivalent has no satisfiable term;
- a formula is a tautology if and only if a CNF equivalent has no falsifiable clause;
- a formula is a contingency when it is satisfiable and not a tautology.

Also explain truth-table method versus normal-form method. Explain that DNF is naturally witness-producing, while CNF is naturally suited for clause checking and later resolution.

